    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-27T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-27T03:00:00-05:00" n="446"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/2828: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-27T09:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 27, 1936—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 27—6:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. By a decree of which advance text is published today Portugal prohibits
                    exportation or transit of arms and munitions of war including <pb facs="0612"
                        n="513" xml:id="pg_513"/> airplanes and ships to Spain. Decree to be
                    suspended in case enlistment or subscriptions of money are effected in signatory
                    countries.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
